# parser-lr

Shift-reduce parser library for EBNF grammars. Builds parse tables and uses them to produce an AST.

## Deliverables

- **Library** — importable from Node and browser npm projects (`dist/lib/`, built with `tsc`)
- **CLI** — Node command-line tool (`bin/parser-lr.js`, built with Rollup)

## Formatting

- **Indentation** — 4 spaces everywhere (TypeScript, JSON, markdown, config). Never tabs.

## Dependencies

- Use **`x` semver wildcards** in `package.json` (e.g. `5.x`, `1.x`), not pinned patch/minor versions
- Do not add runtime or dev dependencies without discussing with the user first

## Layout

- Organize by **domain concepts**, not technical layers (no `controllers/`, `views/`, `services/` folders)
- Library source under `src/lib/`; public API via `src/lib/index.ts`
- CLI under `src/cli/` (Node-only; may import from `src/lib/`)
- Barrel `index.ts` files for directories with multiple related exports

## Build

- `npm run build:lib` — `node scripts/build-lib.mjs` → `dist/lib/` (ESM) and `dist/lib-cjs/` (CommonJS)
- `npm run build:cli` — `rollup -c rollup.cli.config.js` → `bin/parser-lr.js`. The bundle inlines `grammar.json` via `src/cli/bootstrap-meta-grammar.ts`, so the CLI needs no `grammar.json` file at runtime.
- `npm run build` — both, in that order
- `npm test` — Jest (`src/**/*.test.ts`, TypeScript via ts-jest). Expected errors must not reach the console; see **`testing.mdc`**
- `npm run acceptance` — packs the tarball, installs it into a scratch project, and runs the CLI + table-only import smoke checks (verifies the meta-grammar packaging blockers stay fixed)

## Meta-grammar loading

- The bootstrapped `grammar.json` loads **lazily** (first `readGrammar` / `fromGrammar` / `validateGrammarTable` call), never at module import. Table-only consumers (`ParseContext.fromTableJson`) touch no filesystem and no `import.meta`.

## Publish (npm)

- **`package.json`** — npm manifest (`name`, `version`, `exports`, `bin`, `files`, …)
- **`.npmrc`** — default registry (`https://registry.npmjs.org/`)
- **`prepack`** — runs `npm run build` automatically before `npm pack` / `npm publish`
- **`files`** — `bin/`, `dist/`, `docs/`, `grammars/`, plus root `README.md` and `LICENSE`. npm always includes `package.json` as well. `src/` stays out of the tarball.

## Paths

- Use the real project path in docs and examples (e.g. `/Users/amoss/parser-lr`), not placeholders like `/path/to/project`
